  "Qtext": "\n\nIt is given that STUV is a parallelogram and W is a point on the side TU and VW when produced meets ST at point X . Then prove that\n\\[\n\t\\frac{VW }{WX } = \\frac{VU }{TX } \n\\]\nand\n\\[\n\t\\frac{VX }{VW } = \\frac{SX }{VU }\n\\]\n\\newline\ntikzpicture{}\n\\newline\n\n",
  "Steps": [{
    "id": "s1",
    "n_params": 0,
    "step_txt": "Since STUV is a parallelogram, we have $SV \\parallel TU $, and $VU = ST $.\n\nNow, in triangle SXV , we have $TW \\parallel SV $.\n\\[\n\t\\Rightarrow \\frac{WX }{VW } = \\frac{TX }{VU }\n\\]"
  }, {
    "id": "s2",
    "n_params": 0,
    "step_txt": "\n\\[\n\t\\Rightarrow \\frac{WX }{VW } = \\frac{TX }{VU }\n\\]\n\\[\n\t\\Rightarrow \\frac{VW }{WX } = \\frac{VU }{TX }\n\\]"
  }, {
    "id": "s3",
    "n_params": 0,
    "step_txt": "\nNow, adding 1 to both sides of the above equation, we get\n\\[\n\t\\frac{VW }{WX } + 1 = \\frac{VU }{TX } + 1\n\\]\n\\[\n\t\\Rightarrow \\frac{VW + WX }{WX } = \\frac{VU + TX }{TX }\n\\]"
  }, {
    "id": "s4",
    "n_params": 0,
    "step_txt": "\n\\[\n\t\\Rightarrow \\frac{VX }{WX } = \\frac{ST + TX }{TX }\n\\]\n\\[\n\t\\Rightarrow \\frac{VX }{WX } = \\frac{SX }{TX }\n\\]"
  }, {
    "id": "s5",
    "n_params": 0,
    "step_txt": "\nNow, dividing the above two results, we get\n\\[\n\t\\frac{VX }{VW } = \\frac{SX }{VU }\n\\]"
  }, {
    "id": "s6",
    "n_params": 0,
    "step_txt": "\nHence proved\n\\newline\n\n"
  }]
};
